class Solution {
    public int findLUSlength(String a, String b) {
        if (a.equals(b)) {
            return -1;
        } else {
            return Math.max(a.length(), b.length());
        }
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: The solution directly compares the input strings and returns the maximum length if they are not equal, or -1 if they are equal, leveraging the fact that a longer string cannot be a subsequence of a shorter one.
